<!-- TEAM -->
<section>
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="eyebrow">Our Team</div>
    <h2 class="serif-h" style="font-size:48px;margin-bottom:.75rem">Coached by athletes who've done<br>what you're trying to <em>do.</em></h2>
    <p class="body-copy" style="max-width:600px;margin-bottom:0">Every coach on our team has lived the recruiting process, competed at the highest collegiate levels, and navigated the pressures of elite athletics firsthand.</p>
    <div class="team-grid">
      <div class="coach-card">
        <img class="coach-img" src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/b7e516_4bd557b2753a47dbb1d04e25c25e6ec1~mv2.webp/v1/fill/w_291,h_367,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/Screenshot%202026-04-10%20at%2012_40_14%E2%80%AFAM.webp" alt="Mary Lewis" />
        <div class="coach-tags"><span class="coach-tag">WTA Professional</span><span class="coach-tag">Division I Coach</span><span class="coach-tag">All-Big Ten ×2</span></div>
        <div class="coach-name">Mary Lewis</div>
        <div class="coach-title-txt">Professional Tennis Player, Tennis Coach & Mentor</div>
        <p class="coach-bio">Mary Lewis's journey encompasses every facet of competitive tennis — from distinguished collegiate play to the professional circuit on the WTA Tour, and into coaching at the Division I level. At Michigan State University, she earned two-time All-Big Ten selection, team captain, and ITA Cissie Leary Sportsmanship Award honors. She currently holds a WTA singles ranking of No. 658 and a doubles ranking of No. 354.</p>
        <div class="coach-creds"><span class="coach-cred">2× All-Big Ten</span><span class="coach-cred">WTA Singles No. 658</span><span class="coach-cred">ITA Cissie Leary Award</span><span class="coach-cred">D1 Athletic Trainer</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="coach-card">
        <img class="coach-img" src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/f3047b_314ec9dfb6404f6494432fd7dd2818b3~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_291,h_367,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/IMG_6925_edited.jpg" alt="Elizabeth Profit" />
        <div class="coach-tags"><span class="coach-tag">Blue Chip Recruit</span><span class="coach-tag">SMU Program Director</span></div>
        <div class="coach-name">Elizabeth Profit</div>
        <div class="coach-title-txt">Tennis Coach & Mentor</div>
        <p class="coach-bio">Before college, Elizabeth was ranked No. 3 nationally in her class and recognized as a Blue Chip prospect. She competed at Baylor University and the University of Tennessee, navigating the full reality of Division I athletics while managing type 1 diabetes. After her playing career, she served as Director of the SMU Junior Tennis Program for three years.</p>
        <div class="coach-creds"><span class="coach-cred">No. 3 National Junior</span><span class="coach-cred">Baylor & UT Alum</span><span class="coach-cred">SMU Program Director</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="coach-card">
        <img class="coach-img" src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/b7e516_0047a50198f44eb99c27cb8c880bf1b8~mv2.jpeg/v1/fill/w_291,h_367,al_c,q_80,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/IMG_2377.jpeg" alt="Elexis Loving" />
        <div class="coach-tags"><span class="coach-tag">ATC Professional</span><span class="coach-tag">MSAT · Tarleton State</span><span class="coach-tag">D1 Athletic Trainer</span></div>
        <div class="coach-name">Elexis Loving</div>
        <div class="coach-title-txt">Athletic Trainer & Performance Specialist</div>
        <p class="coach-bio">Elexis Loving brings medical and performance expertise as a Certified Athletic Trainer with a Master of Science in Athletic Training from Tarleton State University. She has worked at Stephen F. Austin State University and Michigan State University supporting Women's Tennis programs directly — bridging injury prevention, athlete longevity, and on-court performance.</p>
        <div class="coach-creds"><span class="coach-cred">Certified ATC</span><span class="coach-cred">MSAT · Tarleton State</span><span class="coach-cred">SFA Alum</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
